reviews_data.review_text: Wonderful staff and environment that is conducive for learning and thinking....
They made me feel very welcomed!
The point of a book drop box is so that you can return a book after hours and on holidays- this does not work if you lock your drop box after hours and on holidays.

As a new year challenge, I decided to join a sign language class to exercise my brain at this location. What a wonderful decision! Jen was absolutely amazing! She was patient, engaging, kind, entertaining and a very intriguing person as a whole. She is a natural at teaching. I can also tell that she cares. All the staff at this location was very nice and welcoming. I would advise anyone to look at the library calendar to see all the FREE things they have available at all the locations. Enjoy!
The black guy with the glasses is so nice. He was very supporting of the kids with Autism at our event. He made sure the atmosphere and environment were condusive to the needs of the children.
I love the staff they are always so helpful with helping me master this technology journey
nice library, I come here to do my printing also.
Ms. Jackie and Ms. Jennifer are awesome storytime leaders.  My granddaughter has been coming since she was 6 months old.  Now 3 1/2.   Has helped her to ready for preschool.
I attend a bi-weekly D&D session on thursday nights and we have a blast everytime!

I love going to this library! The librarians/staff are very friendly and helpful, and there are a ton of fun events all year round! I also enjoy that the library cares about its community (i.e., they send surveys asking about what to improve).

Such a warm and welcoming place for any one of any age! I bring my daughter here for story time. The first time we came we were greeted by friendly staff who immediately made us feel welcomed and valued. My daughter loves to play here and is a great place for her to explore. I can’t wait until she is old enough to read to really get her started with all that the library has to offer!
This is a lovely library, the people are wonderful and they offer so much for the kids to do. My grandkids love spending hours here.
Beautiful library with a relaxing and welcoming atmosphere. Great resources and community events.

This is our local library branch, and it's a beautiful building.  We vote here.  I regularly place holds for books that are delivered from other branches so that I can pick up from one convenient location.  I can return books via the drive-up drop boxes.  The staff is very helpful if are looking for something in particular or want a recommendation.  The children's area is well-organized, comfortable, and clean so my young boys like looking around too.

Beautiful library! I’ve been coming here since I was a child & now take my kids. Their storytime for families is lovely, with lots of effort put in. We enjoyed bubbles, music, and of course 3 lovely books read aloud. The staff is always extremely helpful and kind.
Always find what I’m looking for and if I can’t the staff always makes sure to request it from another branch 😊
Staff is super friendly
I've come to this library for years, it's my favorite and I love it^-^
The programs here are top notch, definitely help me find friends and connect with the community!

They are the most friendly and warm welcome librarians I have ever met. There is so much for children: computers, tons of books, fiction, non-fiction, Spanish books, audio and cd movies, for different ages, printer, clean and spacious bathrooms, play corner for little children. Library running app so you can track your returns due, place books on a hold and what books are ready to pick up, so you can scan and check out on your own, return books available 24/7 outside of the building. Our kids love this place a lot! Thank you!
Love this library and its programs. Absolutely love the ASL club and Board Game Night!! The staff is super friendly and helpful. This has been my favorite library ever!
I've only been here several times, primarily to use the computers. It is a clean modern looking library. The librarians are quite pleasant and accommodating if you need help.
Fantastic library! Great staff. Great location. Very cozy.
Staff members are friendly and helpful!
Excellent modern library with a fabulous environment.  Come on out and bring the kids!
Great library! The staff is friendly, the building is cool, and they have fun activities to be a part of. I have made some good friends there though the adult activities.

Just moved here from Oregon and have received the warmest welcome into Charlotte at this wonderful library. The staff are so friendly and attentive and great with children! My daughter and I love going! Five stars all the way.

I love this library and I want to give it a 5, but it can get loud in there at times. There was a time when the employees used their inside voices, but that's out the door. Trying to focus can be a little frustrating!!
The Young Explorers Enrichment Center Summer Campers LOVED IT ❣️ The librarians we're Awesome
Great staff here and they always have a nice selection of books. Very clean
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi, A P! We love to see reviews like yours - and we look forward to your next visit!

reviews_data.review_text: We love this library. It’s a great location, peaceful and beautiful area that’s a great place to relax with a book. It’s clean and well kept. The staff are so friendly and helpful, and have been great in helping us find and order books. My daughter has been on a reading binge and we end up there almost every week and loving it. We are so grateful to have this resource in our community.
